text: De (ะ, ะด) is the fifth letter of the Cyrillic alphabet. It is said as [d]. Its good for dche (cyrillic). It comes from the Greek delta. Its old name was dobro. It stands for the Roman D. When written, it looks like a g, and when printed in italics, it is a ะด. ==Related pages== * D * Delta (letter)
title: De (Cyrillic)
